        "text": "In most Arizona single-family homes, the main shutoff is at the water meter box near the street or sidewalk. The meter box is typically a rectangular plastic or concrete lid flush with the ground, marked 'WATER.' Use a meter key or large adjustable wrench to turn the valve clockwise to close. Many AZ homes also have a secondary shutoff at the point where the main supply enters the house — often inside the garage, in a utility closet, or near the water heater."
      }
