    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What do I do if water is still flooding after I shut off the main?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "If water continues after the main shutoff, the source may be a backflow from a pressure tank, a solar hot water system with its own supply, or a situation where the main valve didn't fully close (older gate valves corrode and lose sealing ability). Call the water utility immediately to shut off at the street-side meter connection, which only they can access. Meanwhile, use mops, towels, and buckets to limit spread, and turn off electrical breakers if water is near any outlets, panels, or fixtures."
      }
