        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "A burst half-inch pipe under typical residential pressure (60–80 psi) can release 50–100 gallons per minute. In one hour, that's potentially thousands of gallons — enough to saturate drywall, flooring, and insulation throughout an entire room and into adjacent rooms. Water damage restoration costs in AZ typically run $3,000–$15,000 for a single-room event. Fast shutoff is the single most effective thing you can do to limit damage."
      }
